♪ For once in my my life ♪

1286
00:56:13.453 --> 00:56:14.705
[both chuckle]

1287
00:56:17.708 --> 00:56:19.543
Here. I brought you something to eat.

1288
00:56:20.127 --> 00:56:21.420
Uh. eat?

1289
00:56:23.463 --> 00:56:24.631
It's tea cake.

1290
00:56:25.465 --> 00:56:26.466
Oh.

1291
00:56:28.969 --> 00:56:30.053
Thanks. Pink.

1292
00:56:31.179 --> 00:56:32.764
-You're very...
-Sweet?

1293
00:56:34.474 --> 00:56:36.310
I know. Everyone tells me.

1294
00:56:37.686 --> 00:56:39.104
I was gonna say thoughtful.

1295
00:56:40.063 --> 00:56:41.106
I like that better.

1296
00:56:44.443 --> 00:56:46.653
It's so hard to be her sister sometimes.

1297
00:56:47.904 --> 00:56:49.239
It's hard to be her friend.

1298
00:56:50.198 --> 00:56:51.575
Do you think Red knows that?

1299
00:56:53.076 --> 00:56:54.161
I don't know. Pink.

1300
00:56:55.329 --> 00:56:56.413
[Hazel] Hey.

1301
00:56:56.496 --> 00:56:58.415
Everyone is in their feelings tonight.

1302
00:56:59.207 --> 00:57:00.542
You should know I feel...

1303
00:57:02.252 --> 00:57:03.503
like I need more dessert.

1304
00:57:03.587 --> 00:57:04.796
[chuckles]

1305
00:57:08.717 --> 00:57:09.885
[door opens]

1306
00:57:09.968 --> 00:57:11.928
[indistinct conversation]

1307
00:57:12.012 --> 00:57:13.555
[giggling] Thank you.

1308
00:57:14.306 --> 00:57:15.891
[Luis chuckles]

1309
00:57:21.396 --> 00:57:22.648
Yeah. um...

1310
00:57:22.731 --> 00:57:24.650
I'll... I'll see you in the morning.

1311
00:57:34.159 --> 00:57:36.119
He's pretty great.

1312
00:57:37.162 --> 00:57:39.122
you know. for an HK.

1313
00:57:40.582 --> 00:57:41.708
[sighs]

1314
00:57:41.792 --> 00:57:42.876
Chloe?

1315
00:57:43.919 --> 00:57:45.545
Please. talk to me.

1316
00:57:45.629 --> 00:57:46.713
Why?

1317
00:57:47.339 --> 00:57:48.924
So you can just ignore me some more?

1318
00:57:51.593 --> 00:57:54.846
It must be so easy for you. Red.

1319
00:57:55.847 --> 00:57:57.182
Flipping back and forth.

1320
00:57:58.767 --> 00:58:00.435
On again. off again.

1321
00:58:00.519 --> 00:58:02.354
Hero. villain. sister. friend.

1322
00:58:04.022 --> 00:58:05.023
I'm envious.

1323
00:58:05.107 --> 00:58:06.108
Really.

1324
00:58:06.733 --> 00:58:08.777
You just ride any wave you want

1325
00:58:08.860 --> 00:58:10.278
to get what you want...

1326
00:58:10.362 --> 00:58:12.030
-Chloe.
-like a true villain.

1327
00:58:12.823 --> 00:58:13.907
Chloe...

1328
00:58:13.990 --> 00:58:15.534
No. it's okay.

1329
00:58:15.617 --> 00:58:18.787
You've been telling me
all along that this is who you really are.

1330
00:58:19.287 --> 00:58:21.957
I guess I'm just realizing
I should have believed you.

1331
00:58:22.040 --> 00:58:23.792
Is this about the chess game?

1332
00:58:23.875 --> 00:58:25.127
Because I'm sorry.

1333
00:58:25.210 --> 00:58:26.878
-but I had to think quickly.
-No!

1334
00:58:26.962 --> 00:58:29.464
It's about you and me.

1335
00:58:30.716 --> 00:58:32.843
I mean. I thought we were friends.

1336
00:58:33.385 --> 00:58:35.095
-A team.
-We are.

1337
00:58:35.178 --> 00:58:38.557
I mean. first. it turns out
I don't actually know my mom at all.

1338
00:58:38.640 --> 00:58:40.350
Which means
that everything I looked up to.

1339
00:58:40.434 --> 00:58:43.145
everything that
I wanted to be means nothing.

1340
00:58:43.812 --> 00:58:45.897
And then. you...

1341
00:58:46.898 --> 00:58:50.068
Ever since we got here.
you've been ignoring me.

1342
00:58:50.152 --> 00:58:52.320
You're against me. You use me.

1343
00:58:52.404 --> 00:58:53.864
Wait. What?

1344
00:58:53.947 --> 00:58:58.910
I thought you'd care.
or at least notice that I'm drowning. Red.

1345
00:58:58.994 --> 00:59:00.162
[Red] So am I.

1346
00:59:00.245 --> 00:59:02.748
You know.
you're criticizing me for being a villain

1347
00:59:02.831 --> 00:59:04.666
when I'm trying to help my mom.

1348
00:59:04.750 --> 00:59:07.335
A mom that finally truly loves me.

1349
00:59:07.419 --> 00:59:08.670
But when it was saving yours.

1350
00:59:08.754 --> 00:59:10.505
who I am seemed to work for you.

1351
00:59:11.089 --> 00:59:12.591
Convenient. Chloe.

1352
00:59:13.133 --> 00:59:14.176
Wow.

1353
00:59:15.260 --> 00:59:17.137
You really don't care. do you?

1354
00:59:17.846 --> 00:59:20.515
You still think I'm some
boring goody two-shoes

1355
00:59:20.599 --> 00:59:21.933
who's just tagging along.

1356
00:59:23.101 --> 00:59:26.188
Yeah. well... if the shoe fits.

1357
00:59:30.567 --> 00:59:31.610
Chloe...

1358
00:59:33.361 --> 00:59:34.362
[door closes]

1359
00:59:35.614 --> 00:59:37.894
[Queen of Hearts]
Help me. Why do I have to do everything?

1360
00:59:37.949 --> 00:59:39.618
[Cinderella] You take that side. pull.

1361
00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:41.661
-[grunts] Ow!
-I know.

1362
00:59:41.745 --> 00:59:43.538
Where is Prince Phillip when you need him?

1363
00:59:43.622 --> 00:59:45.457
We could have hung out with him more.

1364
00:59:45.540 --> 00:59:48.251
but no. you had to go out with Gaston.

1365
00:59:48.335 --> 00:59:50.253
Everybody has their bad boy phase.

1366
00:59:50.337 --> 00:59:51.963
Thank you. Man.

1367
00:59:53.215 --> 00:59:57.010
You know. I should never
have let Maddox come back.

1368
00:59:57.093 --> 00:59:58.178
I knew better.

1369
00:59:58.970 --> 01:00:01.389
[sighs] But I didn't
want to be rude. [scoffs]

1370
01:00:01.473 --> 01:00:02.891
How ridiculous is that?

1371
01:00:02.974 --> 01:00:05.852
Maybe we need to both let go of
what we think we should do.

1372
01:00:09.523 --> 01:00:12.734
♪ Remember how we used
to be in high school? ♪

1373
01:00:12.818 --> 01:00:14.236
♪ Oh. no ♪

1374
01:00:14.319 --> 01:00:15.529
♪ We were so carefree ♪

1375
01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:18.365
♪ Yeah. we would play by our own rules ♪

1376
01:00:19.950 --> 01:00:23.829
♪ Didn't have a road map
Just a recipe book and dust broom ♪

1377
01:00:23.912 --> 01:00:24.913
What a mess.

1378
01:00:24.996 --> 01:00:27.290
♪ But we had hope and we had each other ♪

1379
01:00:27.374 --> 01:00:29.417
♪ And that was enough ♪

1380
01:00:29.501 --> 01:00:30.752
♪ Mm-mm-mm ♪

1381
01:00:31.628 --> 01:00:34.923
♪ I wish I didn't hide
behind the curtain ♪

1382
01:00:35.006 --> 01:00:36.424
♪ Don't wanna hide anymore ♪

1383
01:00:36.508 --> 01:00:40.720
♪ I try to keep things sunny
so I smile till my cheeks start hurtin' ♪

1384
01:00:40.804 --> 01:00:42.055
♪ Mm-mm-mm ♪

1385
01:00:42.138 --> 01:00:44.808
♪ It's all curtsy
Put it on. smile. wave ♪

1386
01:00:44.891 --> 01:00:47.561
♪ Lucky girl Be happy. behave ♪

1387
01:00:47.644 --> 01:00:49.938
♪ But the dark
It tries to consume me ♪

1388
01:00:50.021 --> 01:00:52.816
♪ These days
my daughter sees right through me ♪

1389
01:00:52.899 --> 01:00:57.821
♪ So how can I reach out
when she feels so far away? ♪

1390
01:00:58.321 --> 01:01:00.407
♪ Well. if she's anything like you ♪

1391
01:01:00.490 --> 01:01:03.493
♪ I know she would say ♪

1392
01:01:04.911 --> 01:01:07.455
♪ When it gets dark
Find the light in you ♪

1393
01:01:07.539 --> 01:01:10.208
♪ And when the door slams
Gotta push right through ♪

1394
01:01:10.292 --> 01:01:13.712
♪ When times get tough
She'll know what to do ♪

1395
01:01:13.795 --> 01:01:15.881
♪ We always find a way ♪

1396
01:01:15.964 --> 01:01:18.550
♪ We can't turn time
but we sure can dream ♪

1397
01:01:18.633 --> 01:01:21.720
♪ Maybe we can live
in the space between ♪

1398
01:01:21.803 --> 01:01:24.431
♪ The woman that you see ♪

1399
01:01:24.514 --> 01:01:26.933
♪ And the girl I used to be ♪

1400
01:01:27.017 --> 01:01:29.644
♪ The girl who always had a plan ♪

1401
01:01:29.728 --> 01:01:32.063
♪ The girl who always held my hand ♪

1402
01:01:32.147 --> 01:01:33.940
♪ Through all of my phases ♪

1403
01:01:34.024 --> 01:01:36.818
♪ So slick how quick
the wind changes ♪

1404
01:01:36.902 --> 01:01:38.987
♪ And now it's our turn to break out ♪

1405
01:01:39.070 --> 01:01:40.906
♪ Be brave with new dreams ♪

1406
01:01:40.989 --> 01:01:42.824
♪ The two dreams we made ♪

1407
01:01:42.908 --> 01:01:45.577
-♪ I wish our daughters were near us ♪
-♪ My daughter ♪

1408
01:01:45.660 --> 01:01:48.914
♪ Oh. daughter. if you can hear us ♪

1409
01:01:48.997 --> 01:01:51.458
♪ I hope you know
I'm proud of the girl you are ♪

1410
01:01:51.541 --> 01:01:54.210
♪ And I hope you know
I'm near even when I'm far ♪

1411
01:01:54.294 --> 01:01:55.503
♪ And if you get lost ♪

1412
01:01:55.587 --> 01:01:57.547
[both] ♪ Look inside your heart ♪

1413
01:01:57.631 --> 01:02:00.050
♪ You'll always find a way ♪

1414
01:02:00.133 --> 01:02:02.552
♪ Maybe it's time
that we split the screen ♪

1415
01:02:02.636 --> 01:02:05.639
♪ And maybe it's time
that we let them see ♪

1416
01:02:05.722 --> 01:02:07.349
♪ A different side of me ♪

1417
01:02:07.432 --> 01:02:08.725
♪ A different side of... ♪

1418
01:02:08.808 --> 01:02:10.810
[both] ♪ The girl I used to be ♪

1419
01:02:10.894 --> 01:02:15.565
[♪ both vocalizing]

1420
01:02:18.443 --> 01:02:20.445
[♪ Song fades]

1421
01:02:24.950 --> 01:02:26.910
[Maddox gasps] What are you two up to?

1422
01:02:26.993 --> 01:02:28.662
Get down from there!

1423
01:02:28.745 --> 01:02:30.747
[♪ Ominous music playing]

1424
01:02:32.582 --> 01:02:33.583
[doorknob rattles]

1425
01:02:33.667 --> 01:02:35.460
[Oraculum clicking]

1426
01:02:38.004 --> 01:02:40.048
[cuckoo clock chiming]

1427
01:02:45.971 --> 01:02:47.764
[Chessy] Oh. hello. Max.

1428
01:02:48.598 --> 01:02:50.350
Cat got your tongue?

1429
01:02:50.433 --> 01:02:51.726
I hope not.

1430
01:02:52.227 --> 01:02:53.728
[whispers] We rarely let go.

1431
01:02:54.354 --> 01:02:57.232
I wonder what the Oraculum will show you.

1432
01:02:57.315 --> 01:02:58.900
I'm not planning to use it.

1433
01:02:58.984 --> 01:03:01.236
This... ruined my father.

1434
01:03:01.319 --> 01:03:02.946
Ruined. empowered.

1435
01:03:03.029 --> 01:03:04.489
Potato. pot ah to.

1436
01:03:04.572 --> 01:03:06.324
I'm gonna use it to save someone instead.

1437
01:03:06.408 --> 01:03:10.537
What if I told you
your father was right all these years?

1438
01:03:11.121 --> 01:03:12.539
Ah. yes.

1439
01:03:13.081 --> 01:03:15.208
That's what you really
want to know. isn't it?

1440
01:03:15.750 --> 01:03:16.835
Good news.

1441
01:03:16.918 --> 01:03:20.296
The Oraculum can answer
all your questions.

1442
01:03:20.839 --> 01:03:22.048
[exhales]

1443
01:03:24.634 --> 01:03:25.844
What did my father see?

1444
01:03:27.262 --> 01:03:28.596
And why is it so important?

1445
01:03:28.680 --> 01:03:30.890
-[♪ Ominous music intensifies]
-[lights buzzing]

1446
01:03:31.891 --> 01:03:33.685
-[electricity crackling]
-[Chessy] Showtime.

1447
01:03:33.768 --> 01:03:35.311
[gears whirring]

1448
01:03:36.730 --> 01:03:38.273
[whooshing]

1449
01:03:39.566 --> 01:03:41.359
I am so proud of you. Max.

1450
01:03:41.443 --> 01:03:42.610
[indistinct shouting echoes]

1451
01:03:43.653 --> 01:03:46.448
Get it right
or I'll show you punishment!

1452
01:03:46.531 --> 01:03:49.075
What your heart wants most.

1453
01:03:49.159 --> 01:03:50.326
My time machine.

1454
01:03:50.410 --> 01:03:52.537
When you alter the fabric of time.

1455
01:03:52.620 --> 01:03:54.956
there can be
some unpredictable consequences.

1456
01:03:55.040 --> 01:03:56.499
[Queen of Hearts] Off with her head.

1457
01:03:56.583 --> 01:03:58.168
[Red and Chloe grunting]

1458
01:03:58.251 --> 01:04:00.420
[whooshing]

1459
01:04:03.298 --> 01:04:05.008
Hearts!

1460
01:04:05.091 --> 01:04:06.092
In your time.

1461
01:04:06.176 --> 01:04:08.303
[Red] It's the perfect place
to keep this hidden.

1462
01:04:08.386 --> 01:04:09.429
[Maddox] A pocket watch.

1463
01:04:09.512 --> 01:04:10.930
[Oraculum clanking]

1464
01:04:11.014 --> 01:04:12.474
I'm so proud...

1465
01:04:12.557 --> 01:04:14.350
[voice echoing] There's no time.

1466
01:04:14.434 --> 01:04:15.769
I love you. son.

1467
01:04:15.852 --> 01:04:17.604
[whooshes]

1468
01:04:19.105 --> 01:04:20.106
[Max gasping]

1469
01:04:20.690 --> 01:04:22.067
[Max] The pocket watch exists?

1470
01:04:22.150 --> 01:04:23.693
That life of my father.

1471
01:04:23.777 --> 01:04:25.779
-It was real?
-[Chessy] It was.

1472
01:04:25.862 --> 01:04:26.946
We looked happy.

1473
01:04:27.030 --> 01:04:28.323
And now you're not.

1474
01:04:28.406 --> 01:04:30.325
The redhead stole that life from you.

1475
01:04:30.408 --> 01:04:31.951
[♪ Intense music playing]

1476
01:04:32.035 --> 01:04:34.454
[Oraculum shattering. clanking]

1477
01:04:36.623 --> 01:04:37.957
She lied to you.

1478
01:04:38.041 --> 01:04:40.043
She pretended to be your friend.

1479
01:04:40.710 --> 01:04:42.754
-[Max] No way!
-[objects clattering]

1480
01:04:43.963 --> 01:04:45.340
[sobbing]

1481
01:04:46.841 --> 01:04:48.551
[voice shaking]

1482
01:04:48.635 --> 01:04:50.303
I never should've seen it.

1483
01:04:50.386 --> 01:04:52.138
[Chessy] But now that you have.

1484
01:04:52.222 --> 01:04:53.932
what are you going to do about it?

1485
01:04:54.015 --> 01:04:55.767
[♪ Intriguing music playing]

1486
01:04:56.351 --> 01:04:59.896
You can decide
your own fate and your father's.

1487
01:04:59.979 --> 01:05:02.774
if you can
get your hands on that pocket watch.

1488
01:05:10.406 --> 01:05:12.408
[♪ Stirring music playing]

1489
01:05:14.619 --> 01:05:17.122
You know. Red's not the only one

1490
01:05:17.205 --> 01:05:19.374
who knows where the pocket watch is.

1491
01:05:19.457 --> 01:05:21.960
Anything she can't live without?

1492
01:05:28.383 --> 01:05:31.886
Revenge is a dish best served... blue.

1493
01:05:32.470 --> 01:05:34.889
[Chloe sobbing]

1494
01:05:34.973 --> 01:05:36.975
-[mice squeaking]
-[♪ somber music playing]

1495
01:05:39.269 --> 01:05:42.063
♪ We were friends
We were close ♪

1496
01:05:42.939 --> 01:05:46.901
♪ How could I have
ever known that it would go ♪

1497
01:05:46.985 --> 01:05:49.821
♪ It would go this way ♪

1498
01:05:49.904 --> 01:05:51.281
♪ This way ♪

1499
01:05:51.990 --> 01:05:54.367
♪ Remember when we were cool? ♪

1500
01:05:55.160 --> 01:05:57.453
♪ I always had your back ♪

1501
01:05:58.037 --> 01:06:02.959
♪ Tell me how could you do me like that? ♪

1502
01:06:03.042 --> 01:06:06.045
♪ You're so heartless ♪

1503
01:06:06.129 --> 01:06:07.380
♪ Heartless ♪

1504
01:06:07.463 --> 01:06:09.841
♪ You hit me when my guard was down ♪

1505
01:06:10.425 --> 01:06:13.553
♪ And the hardest part is ♪

1506
01:06:13.636 --> 01:06:16.014
♪ That I let you let me down ♪

1507
01:06:16.097 --> 01:06:19.225
♪ How can you live with yourself? ♪

1508
01:06:19.309 --> 01:06:22.312
♪ You're not who I thought you were
You're someone else ♪

1509
01:06:22.395 --> 01:06:24.981
♪ There's no beating in your chest ♪

1510
01:06:25.732 --> 01:06:28.318
♪ Just the sound of emptiness ♪

1511
01:06:28.401 --> 01:06:29.986
♪ You're heartless ♪

1512
01:06:32.197 --> 01:06:33.531
♪ You played me from the start ♪

1513
01:06:33.615 --> 01:06:35.074
♪ But I've seen all of your cards ♪

1514
01:06:35.158 --> 01:06:37.952
♪ I can see your true intentions ♪

1515
01:06:38.036 --> 01:06:39.871
♪ Now I'm plotting my revenge ♪

1516
01:06:39.954 --> 01:06:41.456
♪ Your persona is pretend ♪

1517
01:06:41.539 --> 01:06:44.292
♪ And I think it's time
you learned your lesson ♪

1518
01:06:44.375 --> 01:06:46.169
♪ Behind that perfect princess ♪

1519
01:06:46.252 --> 01:06:47.879
♪ Is a nasty web of lies ♪

1520
01:06:47.962 --> 01:06:49.214
♪ Hearts are on your clothes ♪

1521
01:06:49.297 --> 01:06:51.174
♪ But you don't feel a thing inside ♪

1522
01:06:51.257 --> 01:06:52.258
♪ You know what you did ♪

1523
01:06:52.342 --> 01:06:56.930
♪ Can't believe you threw
my life away. away ♪

1524
01:06:57.013 --> 01:06:59.599
♪ I'll turn your nightmares to reality ♪

1525
01:06:59.682 --> 01:07:03.394
♪ My only strategy is your tragedy ♪

1526
01:07:03.478 --> 01:07:05.980
♪ You're not who you pretend to be ♪

1527
01:07:06.064 --> 01:07:08.149
♪ Yeah. you're just like me ♪

1528
01:07:08.983 --> 01:07:11.069
♪ 'Cause you're heartless ♪

1529
01:07:11.152 --> 01:07:12.487
♪ Heartless ♪

1530
01:07:12.570 --> 01:07:15.365
♪ And you'll never care how it feels ♪

1531
01:07:15.448 --> 01:07:18.368
♪ 'Cause you broke apart this ♪

1532
01:07:18.451 --> 01:07:21.329
♪ World I thought I had was real ♪

1533
01:07:22.038 --> 01:07:25.124
♪ I feel so betrayed
You switched up my fate ♪

1534
01:07:25.208 --> 01:07:27.335
♪ Now you're gonna get what you gave! ♪

1535
01:07:27.919 --> 01:07:29.754
♪ There's no beating in your chest ♪

1536
01:07:29.837 --> 01:07:30.838
[device warbles]

1537
01:07:30.922 --> 01:07:33.299
♪ Just the sound of emptiness ♪

1538
01:07:33.383 --> 01:07:34.884
♪ You're heartless ♪

1539
01:07:36.844 --> 01:07:38.721
Max? What are you doing here?

1540
01:07:38.805 --> 01:07:40.348
♪ Yeah. I'm rough around the edges ♪

1541
01:07:40.431 --> 01:07:41.766
♪ But I'm not a bad guy ♪

1542
01:07:41.849 --> 01:07:45.144
♪ I can see the pain
that's been hiding in your eyes ♪

1543
01:07:45.228 --> 01:07:46.437
♪ I know how you're feeling ♪

1544
01:07:46.521 --> 01:07:48.189
♪ 'Cause our feelings intertwine ♪

1545
01:07:48.273 --> 01:07:49.691
♪ You seem like you need a friend ♪

1546
01:07:49.774 --> 01:07:51.276
♪ And right now so do I ♪

1547
01:07:51.359 --> 01:07:54.237
♪ You sound so sincere
but it's tough to open up ♪

1548
01:07:54.320 --> 01:07:55.822
♪ I'm angry and I'm hurting ♪

1549
01:07:55.905 --> 01:07:57.448
♪ And it's hard for me to trust ♪

1550
01:07:57.532 --> 01:08:00.243
♪ But here I am anyway
spilling out my guts ♪

1551
01:08:00.326 --> 01:08:01.869
♪ Well. I made you something special ♪

1552
01:08:01.953 --> 01:08:03.204
♪ And it's gonna cheer you up ♪

1553
01:08:03.288 --> 01:08:05.290
♪ Come on. try it on ♪

1554
01:08:05.373 --> 01:08:06.708
♪ You're gonna love it I swear ♪

1555
01:08:06.791 --> 01:08:08.209
♪ No. I couldn't
No. I shouldn't ♪

1556
01:08:08.293 --> 01:08:09.711
♪ No. I wouldn't even dare ♪

1557
01:08:09.794 --> 01:08:11.379
♪ See how it sparkles? ♪

1558
01:08:11.462 --> 01:08:13.047
♪ It's just like you ♪

1559
01:08:13.131 --> 01:08:14.299
♪ A part of me is scared ♪

1560
01:08:14.382 --> 01:08:16.009
♪ But I have nothing to lose ♪

1561
01:08:16.092 --> 01:08:18.094
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1562
01:08:31.858 --> 01:08:33.609
[glass shattering]

1563
01:08:33.693 --> 01:08:34.986
♪ If you want heartless ♪

1564
01:08:35.069 --> 01:08:36.946
♪ I'll show you heartless ♪

1565
01:08:37.030 --> 01:08:39.490
[both] ♪ Crueler than you'll ever be ♪

1566
01:08:39.574 --> 01:08:43.244
♪ I'll be ruthless 'cause the truth is ♪

1567
01:08:43.328 --> 01:08:45.705
♪ You were never true to me ♪

1568
01:08:46.331 --> 01:08:49.375
♪ I feel so betrayed
You should be afraid ♪

1569
01:08:49.459 --> 01:08:52.170
♪ Now you're gonna get what you gave! ♪

1570
01:08:52.253 --> 01:08:54.922
♪ Now we're totally obsessed ♪

1571
01:08:55.006 --> 01:08:57.675
♪ 'Cause the wicked never rest ♪

1572
01:08:58.426 --> 01:09:00.553
♪ There's no beating in your chest ♪

1573
01:09:01.512 --> 01:09:04.015
♪ Just the sound of emptiness ♪

1574
01:09:04.098 --> 01:09:05.516
♪ You're heartless ♪

1575
01:09:05.600 --> 01:09:07.560
-[both panting]
-[♪ foreboding music playing]

1576
01:09:07.643 --> 01:09:09.479
How'd you like
to dig up some buried treasure?

1577
01:09:10.188 --> 01:09:11.397
[chuckles]

1578
01:09:11.481 --> 01:09:13.816
[Chloe and Max laughing sinisterly]

1579
01:09:22.241 --> 01:09:23.242
[Luis sighs]

1580
01:09:24.327 --> 01:09:25.620
I'm not leaving without Chloe.

1581
01:09:26.329 --> 01:09:27.914
She didn't come back last night.

1582
01:09:27.997 --> 01:09:30.583
-Neither did the prodigal son.
-[door opens]

1583
01:09:30.666 --> 01:09:32.585
Max? Where did he go?

1584
01:09:34.087 --> 01:09:35.254
She's still not here?

1585
01:09:35.922 --> 01:09:38.007
I mean. she was pretty upset last night.

1586
01:09:38.800 --> 01:09:40.593
Yeah? What do you know about it?

1587
01:09:40.676 --> 01:09:42.678
[Pink] I couldn't possibly
know anything. right?

1588
01:09:42.762 --> 01:09:43.763
'Cause I'm nice?

1589
01:09:44.472 --> 01:09:45.598
'Cause I'm happy?

1590
01:09:45.681 --> 01:09:49.435
You know. I choose
to find the joy in everything. Red.

1591
01:09:49.519 --> 01:09:51.145
But it doesn't make me naive...

1592
01:09:51.229 --> 01:09:52.688
[gasps] ...or dumb.

1593
01:09:54.691 --> 01:09:56.442
And it doesn't make me blind

1594
01:09:56.526 --> 01:09:58.695
to seeing people who tolerate me.

1595
01:09:58.778 --> 01:10:00.571
instead of actually care about me.

1596
01:10:00.655 --> 01:10:02.365
[Max and Chloe laughing]

1597
01:10:02.448 --> 01:10:03.658
[♪ Intriguing music playing]

1598
01:10:03.741 --> 01:10:04.742
Chloe?

1599
01:10:05.576 --> 01:10:06.577
[shouts] Chloe?

1600
01:10:07.203 --> 01:10:08.246
Where are they going?

1601
01:10:08.329 --> 01:10:09.414
[Red] Chloe?

1602
01:10:10.373 --> 01:10:11.749
Right. Me. too.

1603
01:10:13.376 --> 01:10:14.377
Look.

1604
01:10:14.877 --> 01:10:16.254
Leaving me behind again.

1605
01:10:17.046 --> 01:10:18.673
What am I. disposable?

1606
01:10:18.756 --> 01:10:21.592
Well. maybe you are. If you're just gonna
stand here and take it.

1607
01:10:23.594 --> 01:10:24.595
[exhales]

1608
01:10:26.264 --> 01:10:27.473
Wait for Pink. too!

1609
01:10:29.809 --> 01:10:31.936
I am good at giving advice.

1610
01:10:33.730 --> 01:10:35.231
Where are they running to now?

1611
01:10:35.314 --> 01:10:36.607
[mumbling] I don't know.

1612
01:10:36.691 --> 01:10:38.693
[♪ Curious music playing]

1613
01:10:39.527 --> 01:10:40.611
[Red] Hey. guys!

1614
01:10:40.695 --> 01:10:41.696
We were waiting for you.

1615
01:10:41.779 --> 01:10:43.239
Are we gonna get to the Oraculum?

1616
01:10:44.741 --> 01:10:46.868
And what's with the makeover?

1617
01:10:46.951 --> 01:10:47.952
Red.

1618
01:10:49.245 --> 01:10:51.497
You know. I wasn't having fun anymore

1619
01:10:51.581 --> 01:10:52.707
being good.

1620
01:10:52.790 --> 01:10:54.542
So I decided to do things your way.

1621
01:10:55.126 --> 01:10:57.503
Cruel... ruthless...

1622
01:10:59.672 --> 01:11:03.009
selfish... heartless.

1623
01:11:04.051 --> 01:11:05.178
Like the new me?

1624
01:11:07.346 --> 01:11:08.639
You can thank Max.

1625
01:11:09.891 --> 01:11:12.101
You did this? To my friend?

1626
01:11:12.185 --> 01:11:13.853
How quickly someone's life can change.

1627
01:11:14.979 --> 01:11:15.980
Right?

1628
01:11:16.689 --> 01:11:17.857
Hero to villain.

1629
01:11:17.940 --> 01:11:20.193
A simple flick of the switch or...

1630
01:11:21.444 --> 01:11:22.695
the wind of a watch.

1631
01:11:22.779 --> 01:11:24.447
[♪ Apprehensive music playing]

1632
01:11:24.530 --> 01:11:25.531
Yeah.

1633
01:11:26.407 --> 01:11:27.408
That's right.

1634
01:11:28.284 --> 01:11:29.327
I know what you did.

1635
01:11:30.745 --> 01:11:32.872
How you ruined
my chances at a normal life.

1636
01:11:33.372 --> 01:11:34.874
A life that you now have.

1637
01:11:34.957 --> 01:11:36.959
Max. I never meant for that to happen.

1638
01:11:37.543 --> 01:11:40.004
[rumbling]

1639
01:11:41.047 --> 01:11:42.215
It's time.

1640
01:11:42.298 --> 01:11:43.424
Ominous much?

1641
01:11:44.717 --> 01:11:47.220
Not Princess. just Red. right?

1642
01:11:47.303 --> 01:11:48.596
Maybe I can help with that.

1643
01:11:52.099 --> 01:11:54.185
I'm clearly
out of the loop. but this is bad. right?

1644
01:11:56.562 --> 01:11:57.897
I know what they're after.

1645
01:11:57.980 --> 01:11:58.981
Come on.

1646
01:11:59.065 --> 01:12:01.067
[♪ Intense music playing]

1647
01:12:03.486 --> 01:12:04.529
[Pink] Wait!

1648
01:12:05.696 --> 01:12:06.697
[sighs]

1649
01:12:06.781 --> 01:12:08.366
Come on. Red!

1650
01:12:15.414 --> 01:12:16.791
[dodo screeching]

1651
01:12:17.625 --> 01:12:18.626
Come on.

1652
01:12:19.585 --> 01:12:21.128
We need to get to the center and fast.

1653
01:12:21.712 --> 01:12:23.089
-[Red sighs]
-[Luis] Oh!

1654
01:12:23.172 --> 01:12:25.675
Okay. How about. um... This way. Yeah.

1655
01:12:26.843 --> 01:12:29.345
[Chloe and Max laughing in distance]

1656
01:12:29.428 --> 01:12:30.468
I can hear them. This way.

1657
01:12:30.972 --> 01:12:32.390
[Luis] Whoa! Look out!

1658
01:12:32.473 --> 01:12:34.308
[Chloe laughing]

1659
01:12:35.977 --> 01:12:37.228
[Red] This way.

1660
01:12:37.311 --> 01:12:38.354
[Luis] Where are they?

1661
01:12:43.818 --> 01:12:45.069
-This way.
-No. wait.

1662
01:12:45.653 --> 01:12:47.113
-But we don't have time...
-Wait!

1663
01:12:48.030 --> 01:12:50.533
Three. two. one.

1664
01:12:59.417 --> 01:13:00.418
Come on.

1665
01:13:01.627 --> 01:13:02.795
Luis. there.

1666
01:13:03.838 --> 01:13:05.256
[sighs] We'll never make it.

1667
01:13:05.339 --> 01:13:06.632
Yes. you will.

1668
01:13:06.716 --> 01:13:07.842
-[♪ Heroic music plays]
-Go!

1669
01:13:07.925 --> 01:13:09.302
-[Red] What are you doing?
-Hurry!

1670
01:13:09.385 --> 01:13:11.387
I can't hold them off for long. Go!

1671
01:13:12.054 --> 01:13:14.015
-[walls rumbling]
-Luis!

1672
01:13:14.557 --> 01:13:16.058
-[walls slam]
-No!

1673
01:13:16.142 --> 01:13:18.519
I'll find you. I promise.

1674
01:13:19.145 --> 01:13:20.187
No. no. no. no.

1675
01:13:20.271 --> 01:13:21.772
[Chloe and Max laughing in distance]

1676
01:13:25.484 --> 01:13:26.485
[Red shouts] Chloe?

1677
01:13:26.569 --> 01:13:27.820
Max. keep up.

1678
01:13:30.615 --> 01:13:32.158
-[Max laughs]
-[Red shouting] Chloe?

1679
01:13:33.200 --> 01:13:34.201
Where are you?

1680
01:13:35.703 --> 01:13:36.954
[Chloe's voice] Selfish.

1681
01:13:38.706 --> 01:13:39.916
Ruthless.

1682
01:13:42.084 --> 01:13:43.586
[Max's voice] Ruined my life.

1683
01:13:45.671 --> 01:13:46.923
[Pink's voice] Hard to love.

1684
01:13:48.174 --> 01:13:50.092
[Queen of Hearts]
You're such a disappointment.

1685
01:13:50.176 --> 01:13:51.677
[Chessy] Hearing things?

1686
01:13:52.386 --> 01:13:54.847
Warmer. Warmer.

1687
01:13:54.931 --> 01:13:57.475
Unlike them. I'm not in your head.

1688
01:13:57.558 --> 01:13:59.226
Chessy. leave me alone.

1689
01:13:59.310 --> 01:14:02.229
Not exactly crushing
this whole hero thing. huh?

1690
01:14:02.939 --> 01:14:04.815
I never asked for this.

1691
01:14:04.899 --> 01:14:06.484
Except you kinda did.

1692
01:14:07.485 --> 01:14:09.028
Now they all hate me.

1693
01:14:09.111 --> 01:14:11.364
Well. you did ruin the Hatters' lives.

1694
01:14:11.447 --> 01:14:12.740
got your mom captured.

1695
01:14:12.823 --> 01:14:15.326
left your boyfriend
in a shrub. and. oh. yeah.

1696
01:14:15.409 --> 01:14:18.037
nearly fed your bestie
to a bloodthirsty flower.

1697
01:14:18.996 --> 01:14:22.458
Didn't exactly
figure it out together. did you?

1698
01:14:23.542 --> 01:14:24.835
[voice shaking] Leave me alone.

1699
01:14:24.919 --> 01:14:26.921
[Chloe and Max laughing]

1700
01:14:27.004 --> 01:14:28.422
[laughter fades]

1701
01:14:30.132 --> 01:14:32.134
[♪ Solemn music playing]

1702
01:14:33.260 --> 01:14:35.680
[Red] ♪ I'm so lost and defeated ♪

1703
01:14:35.763 --> 01:14:39.976
♪ I've been climbing
but I keep getting knocked down ♪

1704
01:14:40.059 --> 01:14:42.937
♪ Down. down. down ♪

1705
01:14:44.563 --> 01:14:47.233
♪ How can a villain be a hero? ♪

1706
01:14:47.316 --> 01:14:51.529
♪ I don't even seem to recognize me now ♪

1707
01:14:51.612 --> 01:14:54.407
[♪ vocalizes] ♪ Now ♪

1708
01:14:56.200 --> 01:14:59.537
♪ Every mistake's led me here ♪

1709
01:14:59.620 --> 01:15:04.166
♪ Now it's all up to me ♪

1710
01:15:07.628 --> 01:15:12.341
♪ Will I ever know who I am? ♪

1711
01:15:13.259 --> 01:15:18.222
♪ Will I ever get the chance? ♪

1712
01:15:19.390 --> 01:15:24.770
♪ Can I find the strength
that's deep inside me ♪

1713
01:15:24.854 --> 01:15:29.483
♪ Will ever understand ♪

1714
01:15:29.567 --> 01:15:31.402
♪ Who I am? ♪

1715
01:15:31.485 --> 01:15:34.196
♪ I made a mess and now my... ♪

1716
01:15:34.280 --> 01:15:36.449
♪ My time is running out ♪

1717
01:15:36.532 --> 01:15:40.369
♪ There's no second chances this time ♪

1718
01:15:40.995 --> 01:15:42.872
♪ No. whoa ♪

1719
01:15:42.955 --> 01:15:45.082
♪ This rebel deep inside ♪

1720
01:15:45.166 --> 01:15:47.960
♪ Won't go down without a fight ♪

1721
01:15:48.044 --> 01:15:53.340
♪ Won't give up till I make this right! ♪

1722
01:15:54.300 --> 01:15:55.551
-[exhales]
-[♪ song ends]

1723
01:15:57.928 --> 01:16:01.307
[strange giggling]

1724
01:16:03.559 --> 01:16:05.394
[♪ Melancholy music playing]

1725
01:16:12.443 --> 01:16:14.153
[young Red and young Pink giggling]

1726
01:16:25.706 --> 01:16:27.208
[both giggle]

1727
01:16:33.923 --> 01:16:35.925
[♪ Uplifting music playing]

1728
01:16:42.056 --> 01:16:43.057
Pink!

1729
01:16:44.183 --> 01:16:45.893
Pink. I need you.

1730
01:16:45.976 --> 01:16:47.311
-[Red. from distance] Pink!
-Red?

1731
01:16:49.146 --> 01:16:52.191
That's my sister in there.
and she needs me.

1732
01:16:52.775 --> 01:16:54.443
[angrily] Open up this instant!

1733
01:16:54.527 --> 01:16:56.237
[rumbling]

1734
01:16:56.320 --> 01:16:58.114
Oh. Thanks.

1735
01:17:02.243 --> 01:17:03.244
Red.

1736
01:17:07.665 --> 01:17:08.666
You came.

1737
01:17:08.749 --> 01:17:09.750
Of course.

1738
01:17:10.251 --> 01:17:11.752
That's what sisters do.

1739
01:17:11.836 --> 01:17:12.962
[both chuckle softly]

1740
01:17:14.338 --> 01:17:15.631
Where did you find that?

1741
01:17:16.549 --> 01:17:18.134
I remembered we left it here.

1742
01:17:22.429 --> 01:17:25.224
[both] ♪ Now I know who I am ♪

1743
01:17:25.307 --> 01:17:27.935
[Red] ♪ Who I am ♪

1744
01:17:28.018 --> 01:17:32.189
[both] ♪ I finally have the chance ♪

1745
01:17:32.273 --> 01:17:33.983
[Pink] ♪ Have the chance ♪

1746
01:17:34.066 --> 01:17:39.613
[both] ♪ I can feel
the strength that's deep inside me ♪

1747
01:17:39.697 --> 01:17:44.160
♪ Now I understand ♪

1748
01:17:44.243 --> 01:17:46.787
♪ Who I am ♪

1749
01:17:47.872 --> 01:17:48.873
[giggles]

1750
01:17:48.956 --> 01:17:50.916
Pink. please tell me you still have

1751
01:17:51.000 --> 01:17:53.252
some of those cookies
left from the picnic.

1752
01:17:53.335 --> 01:17:54.336
Sure do.

1753
01:17:56.088 --> 01:17:58.090
[♪ Mystical music playing]

1754
01:18:06.056 --> 01:18:08.767
[echoes] Who's the big sister now?

1755
01:18:11.020 --> 01:18:12.021
Come on. Maddox.

1756
01:18:12.104 --> 01:18:13.647
-Just let us out.
-Please.

1757
01:18:13.731 --> 01:18:14.833
[Queen of Hearts] Think about your son.

1758
01:18:14.857 --> 01:18:16.567
Hmm.

1759
01:18:16.650 --> 01:18:19.278
-[Maddox laughs]
-Should've brought a bigger broom.

1760
01:18:19.361 --> 01:18:21.322
-Time's up. Queens.
-[♪ menacing music playing]

1761
01:18:21.405 --> 01:18:24.116
The pocket watch is nearly mine.

1762
01:18:24.200 --> 01:18:25.326
[laughs sinisterly]

1763
01:18:25.409 --> 01:18:27.745
I'm so proud of you. Max!

1764
01:18:38.964 --> 01:18:39.965
[vault door clangs]

1765
01:18:53.520 --> 01:18:54.521
Finally.

1766
01:18:55.606 --> 01:18:56.607
For my father.

1767
01:18:57.107 --> 01:18:58.484
For the life we could've had.

1768
01:18:59.026 --> 01:19:01.528
-For Red's betrayal.
-And my revenge.

1769
01:19:01.612 --> 01:19:03.322
[♪ Intense music playing]

1770
01:19:03.405 --> 01:19:04.406
Hey. guys.

1771
01:19:05.199 --> 01:19:06.200
Miss us?

1772
01:19:06.283 --> 01:19:07.701
[chuckles] Us?

1773
01:19:09.203 --> 01:19:10.663
Hi!

1774
01:19:10.746 --> 01:19:12.164
-[Pink grunting]
-[ground rumbling]

1775
01:19:12.248 --> 01:19:14.041
[ground rumbling]

1776
01:19:14.124 --> 01:19:16.377
-[vault clanging]
-[Red grunting]

1777
01:19:19.088 --> 01:19:20.547
[coughing]

1778
01:19:21.423 --> 01:19:22.591
[coughs]

1779
01:19:23.509 --> 01:19:25.135
[Pink] Red. are you okay?

1780
01:19:25.928 --> 01:19:26.929
Go. Pink.

1781
01:19:27.012 --> 01:19:28.180
Get the others.

1782
01:19:28.264 --> 01:19:30.766
-[Pink] Okay.
-[♪ Intense music playing]

1783
01:19:30.849 --> 01:19:31.850
Where is it?

1784
01:19:32.601 --> 01:19:34.061
Where's the pocket watch?

1785
01:19:38.691 --> 01:19:40.067
[Chloe chuckles sinisterly]

1786
01:19:42.903 --> 01:19:44.280
Chloe...

1787
01:19:45.781 --> 01:19:47.074
[scoffs]

1788
01:19:47.157 --> 01:19:48.701
Think about what you're doing.

1789
01:19:49.451 --> 01:19:50.494
This isn't you.

1790
01:19:51.078 --> 01:19:52.746
Weren't you listening. Red?

1791
01:19:53.747 --> 01:19:56.041
Of course it's not me. [chuckles]

1792
01:19:56.125 --> 01:19:57.668
Not the me that you knew. anyway.

1793
01:19:58.419 --> 01:19:59.712
[chuckles] No.

1794
01:19:59.795 --> 01:20:02.423
I'm free of her. [laughs]

1795
01:20:02.506 --> 01:20:04.133
[Max] So click the dial. Chloe.

1796
01:20:04.216 --> 01:20:05.759
Our pain will disappear.

1797
01:20:05.843 --> 01:20:08.679
It'll all go away.
and she will be the one left hurting.

1798
01:20:08.762 --> 01:20:10.389
It's the perfect revenge.

1799
01:20:10.931 --> 01:20:13.017
Put our lives back the way they were.

1800
01:20:14.893 --> 01:20:15.894
Do it.

1801
01:20:15.978 --> 01:20:16.979
[chuckles]

1802
01:20:17.521 --> 01:20:20.107
You think I'm doing this for you. Max?

1803
01:20:20.190 --> 01:20:21.650
Or your dad?

1804
01:20:21.734 --> 01:20:23.235
-[laughs]
-[♪ sinister music playing]

1805
01:20:23.319 --> 01:20:24.695
Aw.

1806
01:20:24.778 --> 01:20:26.739
No. I... I've seen the past.

1807
01:20:26.822 --> 01:20:29.533
I've seen that sad story.

1808
01:20:29.616 --> 01:20:32.661
No. I say we turn this around
and look to the future.

1809
01:20:33.162 --> 01:20:34.330
[breathing heavily]

1810
01:20:34.413 --> 01:20:37.624
A future where I'll finally be on top.

1811
01:20:37.708 --> 01:20:38.917
and you'll know what it's like

1812
01:20:39.001 --> 01:20:40.961
to feel invisible and pushed aside.

1813
01:20:41.045 --> 01:20:43.547
A future where I won't need either of you.

1814
01:20:43.630 --> 01:20:45.632
-But I gave you that power.
-And I took it.

1815
01:20:45.716 --> 01:20:46.967
[Red] Chloe. you were right.

1816
01:20:47.051 --> 01:20:48.594
About everything.

1817
01:20:50.220 --> 01:20:51.388
Traveling to the past.

1818
01:20:51.930 --> 01:20:53.390
going back to save your mom.

1819
01:20:54.475 --> 01:20:55.684
changed my life.

1820
01:20:57.061 --> 01:20:59.563
I finally knew
what it was to do something good.

1821
01:20:59.646 --> 01:21:01.607
And that's because you believed in me.

1822
01:21:01.690 --> 01:21:04.651
You showed me that I wasn't a lost cause.

1823
01:21:05.361 --> 01:21:07.988
You had my back every single time.

1824
01:21:09.073 --> 01:21:11.658
I know these last few days
I haven't had yours.

1825
01:21:13.118 --> 01:21:14.119
But I do now.

1826
01:21:15.496 --> 01:21:16.622
I believe in you.

1827
01:21:17.831 --> 01:21:18.832
In us.

1828
01:21:21.418 --> 01:21:22.503
If you do this.

1829
01:21:23.295 --> 01:21:24.463
we lose everything.

1830
01:21:25.672 --> 01:21:26.965
[watch ticking]

1831
01:21:27.049 --> 01:21:28.550
We lose each other.

1832
01:21:28.634 --> 01:21:30.177
[sobbing]

1833
01:21:30.260 --> 01:21:31.720
No. don't listen to her. Chloe.

1834
01:21:31.804 --> 01:21:33.514
Enough! Both of you!

1835
01:21:37.309 --> 01:21:38.644
[Red] ♪ We'll figure it out ♪

1836
01:21:38.727 --> 01:21:40.687
♪ Figure it out together ♪

1837
01:21:42.648 --> 01:21:45.734
♪ Figure it out
Figure it out together ♪

1838
01:21:51.490 --> 01:21:52.533
♪ Figure it out ♪

1839
01:21:52.616 --> 01:21:55.119
[both] ♪ Figure it out together ♪

1840
01:22:01.708 --> 01:22:03.669
[♪ valiant music playing]

1841
01:22:03.752 --> 01:22:05.212
[crackles. clatters]

1842
01:22:07.965 --> 01:22:08.966
[Red] Chloe!

1843
01:22:12.136 --> 01:22:13.220
[Maddox] No!

1844
01:22:13.303 --> 01:22:15.055
[grunting angrily]

1845
01:22:15.139 --> 01:22:16.974
This is your midnight. Maddox.

1846
01:22:17.057 --> 01:22:18.142
Time to go.

1847
01:22:18.225 --> 01:22:19.560
[growls]

1848
01:22:19.643 --> 01:22:22.146
Ace for effort. though.
You really did give it your all.

1849
01:22:22.229 --> 01:22:24.064
-[both chuckle]
-[Maddox laughs sarcastically]

1850
01:22:25.232 --> 01:22:26.233
Maddox...

1851
01:22:26.316 --> 01:22:27.996
[Maddox] We'll see who gets
the last laugh.

1852
01:22:29.236 --> 01:22:30.946
[♪ Intense music playing]

1853
01:22:32.906 --> 01:22:34.116
[Red] Oh. no.

1854
01:22:34.199 --> 01:22:35.284
[screams] No!

1855
01:22:36.368 --> 01:22:37.786
[Chloe] The watch!

1856
01:22:39.163 --> 01:22:40.581
[Max] It's mine.

1857
01:22:40.664 --> 01:22:42.458
[rumbling]

1858
01:22:44.376 --> 01:22:45.586
Max. look out!

1859
01:22:45.669 --> 01:22:47.212
[Max screams]

1860
01:22:47.296 --> 01:22:49.548
[groaning in pain]

1861
01:22:49.631 --> 01:22:51.008
[Max] Please!

1862
01:22:52.885 --> 01:22:54.428
[Chloe and Red grunt]

1863
01:22:54.511 --> 01:22:55.738
[Red] Together on three. Ready?

1864
01:22:55.762 --> 01:22:57.181
One. two. three!

1865
01:22:57.264 --> 01:22:58.700
-[all grunting]
-[Max] It's gonna fall!

1866
01:22:58.724 --> 01:22:59.725
No. no. no!

1867
01:23:00.642 --> 01:23:02.311
[shatters]

1868
01:23:02.394 --> 01:23:04.938
[both panting]

1869
01:23:05.022 --> 01:23:06.398
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

1870
01:23:06.482 --> 01:23:07.483
[Max groans]

1871
01:23:07.566 --> 01:23:09.860
[♪ Mellow music playing]

1872
01:23:19.119 --> 01:23:20.120
[Max] Thank you.

1873
01:23:22.206 --> 01:23:23.540
What about the watch?

1874
01:23:32.174 --> 01:23:33.342
What do we do with it now?

1875
01:23:36.261 --> 01:23:38.514
I'm sorry. Max. but we can't go back.

1876
01:23:39.848 --> 01:23:42.392
This has caused all of us enough pain.

1877
01:23:43.685 --> 01:23:44.686
[sighs]

1878
01:23:45.437 --> 01:23:47.439
Will you still try and help my father?

1879
01:23:47.523 --> 01:23:49.691
I won't abandon you or your dad.

1880
01:23:50.567 --> 01:23:51.652
I promise.

1881
01:23:53.529 --> 01:23:55.531
[♪ Climactic music playing]

1882
01:24:03.830 --> 01:24:05.040
[splashes]

1883
01:24:07.960 --> 01:24:12.839
[female voice reading softly]

1884
01:24:12.923 --> 01:24:14.299
[Maddox] The pocket watch.

1885
01:24:14.383 --> 01:24:15.884
No!

1886
01:24:15.968 --> 01:24:17.427
I will destroy Wonderland!

1887
01:24:17.511 --> 01:24:19.763
-[Red] Come on. let's go!
-[Max] Thanks. Pink!

1888
01:24:19.846 --> 01:24:21.515
-[roof rumbling]
-[Pink] Knock knock.

1889
01:24:21.598 --> 01:24:22.599
[Queen of Hearts] Pink?

1890
01:24:22.683 --> 01:24:24.184
What in the hat?

1891
01:24:24.810 --> 01:24:25.811
[grunts]

1892
01:24:25.894 --> 01:24:27.187
Oh! Get him!

1893
01:24:27.271 --> 01:24:28.981
-A-ha! There.
-[♪ valiant music playing]

1894
01:24:30.440 --> 01:24:32.192
-Over here!
-Hook!

1895
01:24:34.528 --> 01:24:35.654
Now.

1896
01:24:37.281 --> 01:24:39.616
-[screams]
-[chandelier shatters]

1897
01:24:40.784 --> 01:24:42.452
-We did it!
-[grunting]

1898
01:24:42.536 --> 01:24:43.954
Top that. Hatter!

1899
01:24:44.037 --> 01:24:45.515
[Luis] You're not going anywhere. Hatter!

1900
01:24:45.539 --> 01:24:46.748
[chandelier clangs]

1901
01:24:47.332 --> 01:24:48.917
